===Etymology===
[[w:Venetian_language|Venetian]], which likely derives from the [[w:Middle_Greek_language|Middle Gk.]] (''kontoura''), ''small [[vessel]].''

===Noun===
'''gondola'''
#An enclosed car attached to a cable mechanically lifted up the side of a mountain; an enclosed [[ski-lift]].
#A type of train-car with short sides, open on top.
#A small long, narrow boat with a high prow and stern, best known for its use in the canals of [[w:Venice|Venice]].
#The car of a hot-air balloon or [[zeppelin]].


